Step 1: Create a Project Directory

mkdir apache-docker
cd apache-docker

____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
Step 2: Create a Dockerfile
Create a file named Dockerfile:
# Use the official Apache HTTP server image
FROM httpd:2.4

# Copy custom HTML into the web server document root
COPY ./public-html/ /usr/local/apache2/htdocs/

_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
 Step 3: Add HTML Content
Create a folder called public-html:
mkdir public-html

Inside public-html, create an index.html file:
<!-- public-html/index.html -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Apache in Docker</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1> Apache is running inside Docker!</h1>
</body>
</html>
______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

 Step 4: Build the Docker Image
Run the following command in your apache-docker directory:
docker build -t my-apache-server .
______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Step 5: Run the Apache Container
docker run -dit --name apache-container -p 8080:80 my-apache-server

This maps container port 80 to host port 8080.
Visit http://localhost:8080 in your browser.
______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

To Stop and Remove the Container :
docker stop apache-container
docker rm apache-container
